description: Create a service template. The administrator creates a service template to define standardized infrastructure and an optional CI/CD service pipeline. Developers, in turn, select the service template from Proton. If the selected service template includes a service pipeline definition, they provide a link to their source code repository. Proton then deploys and manages the infrastructure defined by the selected service template. For more information, see Proton templates in the Proton User Guide.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the service template.

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: An optional list of metadata items that you can associate with the Proton service template. A tag is a key-value pair. For more information, see Proton resources and tagging in the Proton User Guide. (dict) --- A description of a resource tag. The key of the resource tag. The value of the resource tag.

nested_params.name: key
nested_params.description: The key of the resource tag.

nested_params.name: value
nested_params.description: The value of the resource tag.

nested_items.name: serviceTemplate
nested_items.description: The service template detail data that's returned by Proton.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the service template.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The time when the service template was created.

nested_items.name: description
nested_items.description: A description of the service template.

nested_items.name: displayName
nested_items.description: The service template name as displayed in the developer interface.

nested_items.name: encryptionKey
nested_items.description: The customer provided service template encryption key that's used to encrypt data.

nested_items.name: lastModifiedAt
nested_items.description: The time when the service template was last modified.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the service template.

nested_items.name: pipelineProvisioning
nested_items.description: If pipelineProvisioning is true, a service pipeline is included in the service template. Otherwise, a service pipeline isn't included in the service template.

nested_items.name: recommendedVersion
nested_items.description: The recommended version of the service template.
